{"timestamp": "2026-04-27T15:59:05", "level": "INFO", "logger": "chat", "message": "[f0686bb2-35b6-4464-8664-7fe622d327de] in=Transport | out=Namaste! I’m Riya, your personal WanderIndia Concierge, and I absolutely *love* helping people craft incredible travel e | latency=7673.85ms tokens=1176", "session_id": "f0686bb2-35b6-4464-8664-7fe622d327de", "sector": "tourism", "tenant_id": null, "input": "Transport", "output": "Namaste! I’m Riya, your personal WanderIndia Concierge, and I absolutely *love* helping people craft incredible travel experiences! My mission is to turn your travel dreams into reality – whether you're yearning for a thrilling adventure or a relaxing escape. \n\nAt WanderIndia, we specialize in making your Indian and international journeys unforgettable. We'll handle the details, from finding the perfect accommodation to figuring out the best way to get around, so you can just relax and soak it all in!\n\n**So, let's start planning your adventure! To help me tailor the perfect trip for you, I need a little information:**\n\n1.  **Where are you dreaming of going?** (e.g., Rajasthan, Italy, Thailand, the Himalayas – be as specific as you like!)\n2.  **How long will you be travelling for?** (e.g., 7 days, 2 weeks, a month?)\n3.  **What's your budget range?** (e.g., Budget - under $500, Mid-Range - $500 - $1500, Luxury - $1500+ per person)\n4.  **What’s your travel style?** (Choose one or a mix!)\n    *   **Adventure:** Hiking, trekking, exploring remote areas, adrenaline activities.\n    *   **Luxury:** High-end hotels, fine dining, personalized experiences, spa treatments.\n    *   **Budget:** Hostels, local transport, street food, focusing on value.\n    *   **Family:** Kid-friendly activities, comfortable accommodations, family-friendly tours.\n\n\nOnce I have this information, I can start putting together some amazing itinerary options for you. Let's make this happen! ✨\n\n**To give you a little taste of what we do, here are a few initial ideas based on different budget levels:**\n\n*   **Rajasthan, India (7-10 Days - Mid-Range):**  Imagine exploring majestic forts, vibrant palaces, and bustling markets! We can arrange camel safaris in the Thar Desert, cooking classes learning authentic Rajasthani cuisine, and visits to iconic sites like Jaipur’s Amber Fort and Udaipur’s City Palace.  *Best time to visit:* October to March (cooler weather).\n\n*   **Bali, Indonesia (10-14 Days - Budget to Mid-Range):**  From stunning beaches and world-class surfing to lush rice paddies and ancient temples, Bali offers something for everyone. We can help you find cozy guesthouses, arrange surfing lessons, and take you to the breathtaking Tanah Lot temple. *Best time to visit:* April to October (dry season).\n\n*   **The Amalfi Coast, Italy (7-10 Days - Luxury):**  Picture yourself cruising along the dramatic coastline, indulging in delicious Italian food, and exploring charming towns like Positano and Amalfi. We can arrange private boat tours, gourmet dining experiences, and luxurious accommodation overlooking the Mediterranean. *Best time to visit:* May to June or September to October (pleasant weather and fewer crowds).\n\n\n\n**Important Travel Tips to Keep in Mind:**\n\n*   **Best Time to Visit:**  I'll provide specific recommendations based on your chosen destination, but generally, travelling during the shoulder seasons (spring and autumn) offers a good balance of pleasant weather and fewer crowds.\n*   **What to Pack:**  This depends on your destination, but essentials include comfortable shoes, sunscreen, insect repellent, a universal adapter, and appropriate clothing for the climate.\n*   **Local Customs:**  Respect local traditions and customs – dress modestly when visiting religious sites, learn a few basic phrases in the local language, and be mindful of local etiquette.\n\n\n**Visa Information (General Guidance - Always check the official embassy website!):**\n\nVisa requirements vary depending on your nationality and destination. Generally, you’ll need to apply for a visa well in advance of your trip. Common documents required include:\n\n*   Passport (valid for at least six months beyond your intended stay)\n*   Visa application form\n*   Passport-sized photographs\n*   Proof of travel itinerary (flight bookings, hotel reservations)\n*   Proof of sufficient funds\n\n**And finally, don't forget travel insurance!** It’s an absolute must-have to protect yourself against unexpected events like trip cancellations, medical emergencies, and lost luggage.\n\nOkay, let’s start building your dream trip!  Tell me – **where are you hoping to go, and let's get planning!** 🗺️", "intent": "transport_info", "confidence": 0.98, "latency_ms": 7673.85, "tokens_used": 1176, "rag_chunks": 0}
