{"timestamp": "2026-07-23T15:58:19", "level": "INFO", "logger": "llm", "message": "LLM /v1/chat/completions ok messages=1 latency=273.72ms tokens=336 out={\"intent\": \"general_query\", \"confidence\": 0.90, \"params\": {}}", "endpoint": "/v1/chat/completions", "messages_count": 1, "max_tokens": 200, "temperature": 0.1, "system_prompt_preview": "", "user_message": "You are an intent classifier. Given a user message and a list of possible intents, classify the message into the most appropriate intent.\n\nINTENTS:\n- order_tracking: User wants to track an order or check delivery status\n- refund_request: User wants a refund for an order\n- return_request: User wants to return a product\n- product_inquiry: User asks about a product's features, price, or availability\n- payment_issue: User has a payment or billing problem\n- complaint: User is unhappy and wants to file a complaint\n- general_query: General question that doesn't fit other intents\n\nUSER MESSAGE: \"hi\"\n\nRespond ONLY with a JSON object in this exact format, nothing else:\n{\"intent\": \"<intent_name>\", \"confidence\": <0.0-1.0>, \"params\": {}}\n\nIf the user mentions specific entities (order ID, date, doctor name, location, amount), extract them into the \"params\" dict.\n\nExamples:\n- \"Where is my order #12345?\" -> {\"intent\": \"order_tracking\", \"confidence\": 0.95, \"params\": {\"order_id\": \"12345\"}}\n- \"I want to book an appointment with Dr. Sharma\" -> {\"intent\": \"book_appointment\", \"confidence\": 0.92, \"params\": {\"doctor_name\": \"Dr. Sharma\"}}\n", "output": "{\"intent\": \"general_query\", \"confidence\": 0.90, \"params\": {}}", "tokens_used": 336, "latency_ms": 273.72}
